					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-708022#post-2006735</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-708022/scp-1126#post-2006735</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 05 Apr 2014 21:24:15 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1472934</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Sigh…<em>Must</em> I continue to act as the SCP Nazi? If this thing existed, the Foundation would want to contain it because the general public knowing about it would demolish any understanding of &quot;normal&quot; or &quot;possible&quot;, so it qualifies as a scip. It's also not a spoof on any aspect of the Foundation, in-universe <em>or</em> out-of-universe (or however you say it), in any way, shape, or form, it doesn't do things that are trivial and/or nonsensical (in terms of scips), and honestly, if it was real, it would have some pretty disturbing implications. What about Agent Moss and Agent Beetle? If T.R.O.P.I.C. existed, the Foundation would <em>need</em> to contain it, it would be no laughing matter. It's like SCP-504 - it's funny, but if you really think about it, the things it could mean would be quite problematic.</p> <p>Obviously, I upvoted this enthusiastically. XD</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
